{
  "stem": "1965.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 99.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And this is how my two brothers and myself came into the house of Madam Rosie Rothschild.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "This lady is also one of the reasons, besides my parents, why I am presenting this story.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "She saved my life.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And it is in this house that I learned, finally, what the war was all about.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Madam Rosie Rothschild was the directress of a home of children who were being hidden from the Gestapo.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The Germans knew of her, but for some reason, they still let her be.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It is not-- it wasn't always that way.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But in that moment, she was still able to save children.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And we were 144 strong-- if I'm not mistaken-- children that were being placed.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And the day when my brother Sam, and Jack, and myself went to her, we three-- and a little boy, and another little girl by the name of Anneke-- we were standing there, watching 60 children being taken away by the Gestapo.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So we stood there, and it was empty suddenly-- all the children gone.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And then came a whole new group of children.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "It is in that house that I learned the true fear of life as a hidden child in Belgium.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And there are certain stories I like to tell about this particular residence.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In [NON-ENGLISH], Antwerpen.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was a large, official building right on the street-- main entrance and a side entrance.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The side entrance led to a school known as [NON-ENGLISH] School, a Jewish school.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The school itself and the building had a common backyard.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It also had, on this side, a library of books by the hundreds-- all Hebrew Jewish books.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And one day, they came to ransack the whole school.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
